welcome to the alfred m spormann laboratory alfred m spormann laboratory home members members of the spormann lab teaching courses offered by alfred m spormann publications spormann lab pubs contact contacting the spormann lab welcome to the alfred m spormann laboratory research interests in our lab are at the interface of fundamental metabolic processes of anaerobic microorganisms and their application in bioenergy bioremediation and human intestinal health our specific research activities range from generating a fundamental understanding of molecular mechanisms of enzymes reactions and pathways to deconvoluting and engineering ecologically robust metabolic processes our research is broadly organized into three areas biochemistry genomics and ecophysiology of reductive dehalogenation metabolic redox processes in biogeochemistry and bioenergy metabolic processes and microbial interactions in human intestinal microbial communities biochemistry genomics and ecophysiology of reductive dehalogenation 0 february 08 2009 lab links research redox dehalogenation gut microbes strain database group meeting bioinformatic tools protocols clark network user login login with your sunetid username password create new account request new password
